<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
[1]
Date: Mon, 29 Aug 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: RIA Novosti, 29 Aug 2005 [edited]
<http://en.rian.ru/russia/20050829/41243474.html>

Cattle vaccination against foot-and-mouth starts in Russian Far East
--------------------------------------------------------------------
A large-scale vaccination program to protect cattle from FMD has begun in
Russia's far-eastern Maritime Territory, a local agricultural department
official said Monday. Alexander Tabachenko said over 150 000 vaccine doses
against the Asia 1 (FMDV-Asia 1) virus had been delivered to the region, and
160 000 more were expected in the next few days. This will allow all cattle at
state and private farms to be vaccinated.
The spokesman said more than 2500 large cattle and 1000 small [livestock] had
already been vaccinated in the Spassky district, and the program was also
under way in the Pozharsky, Kirovsky, and Dalnerechensky districts, where the
disease was also discovered.
Quarantine has been imposed in Spassky district since 26 Aug 2005, and all the
markets where farmers usually sell meat and milk are closed, a spokesman for
the local authorities said.
Measures to prevent the spread of the disease include a move to draw up a
comprehensive register of cattle in Maritime Territory, and a ban on free
cattle transportation, the spokesman said.
[Byline: Anatoly Ilyukhov]
