[2]
Date: Mon, 29 Aug 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Interfax, China, 29 Aug 2005 [edited]
<http://www.interfax.cn/showfeature.asp?aid=5078&slug=CHINA-RUSSIA-FOOT%20AND%
20MOUTH>

More foot-and-mouth cases suspected in Russian Far East
-------------------------------------------------------
Specialists are in Russia's Primorye region near the Chinese border
to investigate the possible spread of foot-and-mouth disease to more
cattle, according to local government officials.
Physicians, epidemiologists and veterinarians have traveled from
Vladivostok to the Spassky district in Russia's Primorye region to
diagnose 15 cows suspected of contracting the foot-and-mouth disease,
the Primorye civil defense and emergencies agency told Interfax.
Earlier, about 150 FMD cases were registered in the Bikino and Vyazemsky
districts of Russia's Khabarovsk region, which borders China. All sick animals
diagnosed with the FMD virus type Asia 1 were culled.
China's Ministry of Agriculture has said they have no information that the
disease has crossed the border and would take immediate action if such an
event occurred. [It seems at least as likely that the disease crossed into
Russia from China. - Mod.JW].
